<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>{{ title }}</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
  <p>
    Semantic profile and contract for clients consuming the CBRWS HAL
    API.
  </p>
  <div>
    <span>profile URI: <code>{{ profile_url }}</code></span>
    <span>schema URI: <code>{{ schema_url }}</code></span>
    <span>media: <code>application/hal+json; profile="{{ profile_url }}"</code></span>
    <span>relations base: <code>/profiles/cbrws/v1/rels/{rel}</code></span>
  </div>
</header>

<main>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This document describes the structure and semantics of the API’s
      discovery document (<code>/api</code>) and its link relations,
      using HAL  (Hypertext Application Language) with CURIEs for
      custom relations.
    </p>

    <p>
      The CBRWS API is a simple web service that provides an endpoint
      (i.e. URL) to serve a greeting message to the user. This
      webservice is used as full production-quality example of how
      to implement a RESTful API using Python's Starlette framework.
    </p>
    <p>
      One important part of being REST-ful, is for the API to be
      discoverable, meaning that clients can find out what resources
      (i.e. endpoints) are available and how to interact with them.
      This is typically done using a discovery document, which is a
      machine-readable representation of the API's structure and
      semantics.
    </p>
    <p>
      For this web service that discovery document is available at
      <code>/api</code> and is formatted using HAL with CURIEs for
      custom relations. This means that the document includes links to
      other resources in the API, as well as metadata about those
      resources. (A CURIE is a Compact URI, which is a way to
      abbreviate long URIs using a prefix and a suffix.)
    </p>
    <p>
      This profile URL (<code>{{ profile_url }}</code>) is both
      an identifier for the profile (as per RFC 6906) and a
      documentation page describing the structure and semantics of
      the response from <code>/api</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
      This document exists in two forms: a human-readable HTML
      document (what you’re reading now) and a machine-readable JSON
      Schema. Clients can request the JSON Schema by sending an
      <code>Accept: application/schema+json</code> header to this URL.
      The JSON Schema can be used to validate that the response from
      <code>/api</code> conforms to the expected structure.
    </p>

    <p>
      That is, this document (and it's machine-readable JSON counterpart)
      describes what /api should return.
    </p>

    <p>
      Clients should treat HAL payloads that include
      <code>profile="{{ profile_url }}"</code> as conforming to
      the contract below.
    </p>

    <p>For machine-readable validation, request this URL with
      <code>Accept: application/schema+json</code> to receive a JSON
      Schema. With <code>Accept: text/html</code> (or a browser),
      you’re viewing this human-readable documentation.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Discovery Document Contract (<code>/api</code>)</h2>
    <p>The discovery resource MUST be a JSON object with the following top-level members:</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>title</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Display name of the API (e.g., “CBRWS API”).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>version</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>API version string (e.g., “1.0”).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>description</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Optional human-readable description.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>_links</code></td><td>object</td><td>Yes</td><td>HAL link collection (see below).</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>_links (HAL &mdash; Hypertext Application Language)</h3>
    <p>The <code>_links</code> object MUST include these members:</p>

    <div>
      <div>
        <h4><code>self</code></h4>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Member</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>href</code></td><td>URI</td><td>Yes</td><td>Absolute URL of the discovery doc (e.g., <code>…/api</code>).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>type</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Media type, e.g. <code>application/hal+json; profile="{{  profile_url }}"</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>profile</code></td><td>URI</td><td>Yes</td><td>Profile identifier <code>{{ profile_url }}</code>.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h4><code>curies</code></h4>
        <p>An array of CURIE (Custom URI) definitions used to compact custom relation names.</p>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Member</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Prefix used in link relations (e.g., <code>cbrws</code>).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>href</code></td><td>URI template</td><td>Yes</td><td>Template for expanding relations (e.g., <code>…/rels/{rel}</code>).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>templated</code></td><td>boolean</td><td>Yes</td><td>Must be <code>true</code> when <code>{rel}</code> appears in <code>href</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>media_type</code></td><td>string</td><td>No</td><td>Hint of representation returned when dereferenced (e.g., <code>application/schema+json</code>).</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>profile</code></td><td>URI</td><td>No</td><td>Profile URI for the doc returned by the CURIE.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p><strong>Expansion:</strong> <code>cbrws:greet</code> → <code>{{ profile_url }}/rels/greet</code></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4><code>cbrws:greet</code></h4>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Member</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>href</code></td><td>URI</td><td>Yes</td><td>Absolute URL of the greet endpoint (e.g., <code>…/api/greet</code>).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>rel</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Literal relation name; MUST be <code>"name"</code>.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>media_type</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Expected response media type (HAL+JSON with this profile).</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>profile</code></td><td>URI</td><td>Yes</td><td>Profile identifier <code>{{ profile_url }}</code>.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Example Discovery Response</h2>
    <pre><code>{
  "title": "CBRWS API",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "This is the API endpoint for the cbrws web service.",
  "_links": {
    "self": {
      "href": "http://localhost:8000/api",
      "type": "application/hal+json; profile=\"{{ profile_url }}\"",
      "profile": "{{ profile_url }}"
    },
    "curies": [
      {
        "name": "cbrws",
        "href": "{{ profile_url}}/rels/{rel}",
        "templated": true,
        "media_type": "application/schema+json",
        "profile": "{{ profile_url }}"
      }
    ],
    "cbrws:greet": {
      "href": "{{ profile_url }}",
      "rel": "greet",
      "media_type": "application/hal+json; profile=\"{{ profile_url }}\"",
      "profile": "{{ profile_url }}"
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
    <p>Tip: clients can validate this against the JSON Schema returned by this same URL when requesting <code>Accept: application/schema+json</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div>
      <h2>Relation Docs (CURIE expansion)</h2>
      <p>Custom relations are documented at <code>/profiles/cbrws/v1/rels/{rel}</code>.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>cbrws:greet</code> → <code>/profiles/greet/v1/rels/greet</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>Each relation supports content negotiation: HTML for humans, JSON Schema for machines.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2>Content Negotiation</h2>
      <p>Supported on this document:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>text/html</code> → this page</li>
        <li><code>application/schema+json</code> → JSON Schema</li>
      </ul>
      <pre><code># HTML
curl -H "Accept: text/html" http://localhost:8000/profiles/cbrws/v1

# JSON Schema
curl -H "Accept: application/schema+json" http://localhost:8000/profiles/cbrws/v1</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Compliance Checklist</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>/api</code> includes <code>title</code>, <code>version</code>, <code>_links</code>.</li>
      <li><code>_links.self</code> has <code>href</code>, <code>type</code>, <code>profile</code>.</li>
      <li><code>_links.curies[0]</code> sets <code>name</code>, <code>href</code> with <code>{rel}</code>, and <code>templated=true</code>.</li>
      <li><code>_links["cbrws:greet"]</code> has <code>href</code>, <code>rel="greet"</code>, <code>media_type</code>, <code>profile</code>.</li>
      <li>Dereferencing CURIEs returns docs/schema via content negotiation.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

